# Supabase Persistence Rules (legacy path)

Use when **`SAQ_DATABASE_PROVIDER=supabase`** or when editing Supabase clients/migrations. For the **Postgres/Drizzle** path, see **`postgres-persistence.mdc`**.

Applies to `src/lib/supabase/`, Supabase-oriented repository code paths, and `supabase/migrations/`.

## Persisted Runtime State

- `profiles` (per auth user; optional display fields)
- `assessments` (includes `owner_user_id`)
- `assessment_collaborators` (per-assessment access: `user_id`, `role`, `invited_by`; owner represented here as well)
- `assessment_scope_selections`
- `assessment_answers`
- `assessment_action_items` (metadata fields such as effort/leader/deadline/status/remarks)

RLS may use `SECURITY DEFINER` SQL helpers for membership checks (e.g. to avoid recursion on `assessment_collaborators`). See migrations and `docs/SAQ_SUPABASE_SETUP.md`.

## Not Persisted

- Static questionnaire configuration.
- Derived results: completion summaries, pass/target outcomes, priorities, recommendations, interpretations.

## Repository Boundary Rules

- Keep Supabase access inside repository/client modules.
- Map DB rows to domain types in repositories; keep UI and engine unaware of DB row shape.
- Prefer idempotent upsert/update patterns for per-assessment runtime tables.
- Do not add questionnaire structure tables unless the architecture decision is explicitly changed.

## Safe Migration Practices

- Additive schema changes first; avoid destructive changes without migration plan.
- Keep migration intent documented in `docs/SAQ_SUPABASE_SETUP.md` when setup steps change.
